summary: An ordinance setting aside all of Queen Anne Boulevard, as widened, extended, laid out and established by Ordinance No. 16790, of the City of Seattle, including street intersections, all portions of streets widened under Ordinance No. 16790, together with all lands and premises condemned and appropriated under said ordinance, for park, parkway, boulevard purposes and transferring the control and jurisdiction thereof unto the Board of Park Commissioners subject to certain reservations and conditions.
